                <note rend="inline" type="source">883.5122/3: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Minister in Egypt</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Gunther</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1929-10-08T14:00:00-05:00"
                            >October 8, 1929—2 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>42. Your despatch No. 252, August 26,<note n="41" xml:id="d977fn41">Despatch not
                        printed; for its enclosure, see <hi rend="italic">supra</hi>.</note>
                    regarding Gaffir Tax. In view of the eradication of the irregularities in the
                    administration of this tax in the interior which existed in 1924 you may, if and
                    when the other Powers enjoying capitulatory rights in Egypt consent to the
                    collection of this tax from their nationals, inform the Egyptian Government that
                    this Government consents to the collection of the Gaffir tax from its nationals
                    resident in Egypt effective from the date when notice of this Government’s
                    consent is given to the Egyptian Government.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Stimson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
